This document describes how to make debian packages by manually.


# Create gcc-stage1 package

PKG_TARGET=ubuntu20 \
SECT=release \
DEBIAN=debian_stage1 \
PROJ=riscv64-gcc-stage1 \
VER=12.0.1-rvv \
  ./pkg_script/ubuntu_package.sh

# Create gcc package

PKG_TARGET=ubuntu20 \
SECT=release \
DEBIAN=debian_stage2 \
PROJ=riscv64-gcc \
VER=12.0.1-rvv \
  ./pkg_script/ubuntu_package.sh


Debian package and related files are generated on pkg_${PKG_TARGET}/
(ex. pkg_ubuntu20) directory.
